com.ibm.portal.state.accessors
Interface AccessorFactory

All Known Subinterfaces:
BooleanAccessorFactory, CheckedURLAccessorFactory, DeletePortletActionAccessorFactory, EngineActionAccessorFactory, ExpansionStatesAccessorFactory, LocaleAccessorFactory, LoginActionAccessorFactory, LogoutActionAccessorFactory, MovePortletActionAccessorFactory, NavigationShiftAccessorFactory, PageModeAccessorFactory, PortletAccessorFactory, PortletStateManagerService, PortletTargetAccessorFactory, ResolvedUrlAccessFactory, ScreenTemplateAccessorFactory, SelectionAccessorFactory, ShowToolsAccessorFactory, SoloAccessorFactory, StateAccessorFactory, StatePartitionAccessorFactory, ThemeTemplateAccessorFactory, URLAccessorFactory
public interface AccessorFactory

Tagging interface to be sub-classed by specific accessor factory interfaces. Accessor factories must not be shared across threads and must not be kept in global variables. To access a specific accessor factory the getAccessorFactory method of the StateManager is used. The class object to this method identifies the interface of the accessor factory to retrieve.

Since:
5.1
